I turned on my laptop and inserted the memory into
the port on the right side. After waiting for
about three seconds, a folder automatically opened
and I found a video file.

parameters.name: マウス・ダブルクリック01

parameters:
\#... I hovered the cursor over the file and
double-clicked on it. When I did that... the
laptop made a clicking sound and launched a video
player, playing the file----...

\n<Minato Neon>(...As I thought. It seems that the password is
inside this video.)

The video was about 15 minutes long, and it would
be a bit troublesome to watch it all. However... I
couldn't afford to miss the password, so I stared
at the screen intently.

\n<Minato Neon>(I hope I can find it quickly... sigh... I hope
there aren't any puzzle elements or anything...)

I couldn't help but let out a sigh... but I
quickly changed my mindset. And then... as if
resonating with me, the screen switched to a
simple black background with only text displayed
on it----...
\n<Minato Neon>...Huh...

My whole body froze at the unexpected footage...
but it was only for a moment.
\n<Minato Neon>\F[\V[2]] W-What was that just now...

\F[\V[2]]... I instinctively closed the video
file. Then, I quickly looked around and confirmed
that I was alone in the room.

\n<Minato Neon>\F[\V[2]] (Are you telling me to watch that just
now... to show me such a video...)

I felt angry at the prank-like setup. However...
if I were to confront Director Udo without
watching the video, I felt like I would be made a
fool of.

\n<Minato Neon>\F[\V[2]] (It's irritating to think that I would
be seen as a child for being shaken up by
something like this... And if this is also part of
the lesson, then if I were to play Reiko...)

I excitedly reached out my hand towards the
laptop. But... I couldn't help but be curious
about the entrance right behind me, so I walked
towards the door.

I felt relieved as I confirmed the simple key
prepared on the door. And when I closed it... I
turned my attention back to the display once
again----...
